data_usage: Global temperature change (relative to 1901-1960) is plotted as a historical time series for all forcings, and for natural forcings only. The 5th to 95th percentile range of model values is also plotted.
methodology:
Methods are those used in Huber and Knutti (2012). The following CMIP5 models were used in the multi-model mean:

bcc-csm1-1, BNU-ESM, CanESM2, CCSM4, CNRM-CM5, CSIRO-Mk3-6-0, FGOALS-g2, GFDL-CM3, GFDL-ESM2M, GISS-E2-H, GISS-E2-R, HadGEM2-ES, IPSL-CM5A-LR, IPSL-CM5A-MR, MIROC-ESM-CHEM, MIROC-ESM, MRI-CGCM3, and NorESM1-M.
